clauses.clause:
Standards are as follows: The classification file must include the following:
Job descriptionsJob descriptions must: Describe the duties and responsibilities of the job concisely, using bias free language;Contain the information required to evaluate the job using the Executive Group Job Evaluation Standard, including:
General accountability;
Organization structure;
Nature and scope of duties;
Dimensions; and
Specific accountabilities;Contain the following identifying information:
Position title;
Position group and level;
Organization;
Branch/division;
Position number;
Geographic location; and
National Occupational Classification (NOC) code;Be updated and evaluated within one year when affected by significant changes, including but not limited to mandate, organizational structure, dimensions or reporting relationships;Be authorized, signed and dated by the immediate manager (when the position reports to the deputy head, the deputy head must authorize, sign and date the job description); andIndicate the effective date.
Organizational charts Organizational charts must: Depict the organizational location of the position and its relationship to the other positions in the same work unit;Represent the organizational structure described in the job description; andBe authorized, signed and dated by the immediate manager (when the position reports to the deputy head, the deputy head must authorize, sign and date the organizational chart).
Job evaluation rationaleThe job evaluation rationale must: Provide the justification for occupational group allocation;Identify and justify the degrees and points chosen for each factor and sub‑factor;Include a comparative analysis of the position to the benchmarks in the Executive Group Job Evaluation Standard; andInclude an analysis of the relevant organizational and inter-organizational relativity used to confirm the decision; andBe signed and dated by the evaluator(s).
Classification action formThe classification action form must: Describe the nature of the action or decision;Identify the ratings and effective date; andBe signed and dated by the deputy head or, in the case of classification actions, be signed and dated by the head of human resources.
Other itemsOther items included in the classification file may include the following: Information that substantiates the selection of the effective date; and Any other data, reports or information that substantiate the classification decision.
